sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User<br/>kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as kueue-webhook-service<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as kueue-controller-manager<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant Cache as In-Memory Cache
    participant Scheduler as Scheduler
    participant Job as Batch Job / Training Job
    participant Pod as Pod

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 1: Job Submission and Admission

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create job<br/>Bearer Token (User)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-batch-v1-job<br/>mTLS (API Server client cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject queue annotation<br/>Suspend job
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Job spec
    K8sAPI-->>User: Job created (suspended)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Job resources<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Job created event

    Controller->>Controller: Create Workload CR<br/>from Job spec
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Workload<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Workload resources<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Workload created event

    Controller->>Cache: Update queue state
    Cache->>Scheduler: Evaluate admission
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Check quota, priority, cohort

    alt Workload admitted
        Scheduler-->>Controller: Admission decision: Admit
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Patch Job (unsuspend)<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
        K8sAPI->>Job: Unsuspend job
        Job->>Pod: Create pods
    else Workload pending
        Scheduler-->>Controller: Admission decision: Pending
        Controller->>Cache: Keep in queue
    end

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 2: Metrics Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>Metrics Scraper

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    Controller-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics<br/>(pending workloads, admitted workloads)

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 3: Visibility API Query

    User->>K8sAPI: GET /apis/visibility.kueue.x-k8s.io/v1beta1/clusterqueues/{name}/pendingworkloads<br/>Bearer Token (User)<br/>K8s RBAC
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Aggregated API call<br/>In-process
    Controller->>Cache: Query pending workloads<br/>In-memory
    Cache-->>Controller: Pending workload list
    Controller-->>K8sAPI: JSON response
    K8sAPI-->>User: Pending workloads

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 4: Multi-Cluster Job Dispatching (MultiKueue)

    participant RemoteK8s as Remote K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    Controller->>RemoteK8s: Create Job in remote cluster<br/>Kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteK8s-->>Controller: Job created
    Controller->>RemoteK8s: Watch remote Job<br/>Kubeconfig credentials
    RemoteK8s-->>Controller: Job status updates

    Note over User,Pod: Flow 5: Provisioning Request (Autoscaling)

    participant ClusterAutoscaler as Cluster Autoscaler
    participant CloudProvider as Cloud Provider API

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ProvisioningRequest<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    ClusterAutoscaler->>K8sAPI: Watch ProvisioningRequest<br/>Bearer Token (ServiceAccount)
    K8sAPI-->>ClusterAutoscaler: PR created event
    ClusterAutoscaler->>CloudProvider: Provision nodes<br/>Cloud credentials
    CloudProvider-->>ClusterAutoscaler: Nodes created
    ClusterAutoscaler->>K8sAPI: Update PR status
